source_jobs.description:
Roosh Investment Group шукає Head of Debt Instruments — senior-level лідера, який очолить новий напрямок debt financing та private credit всередині групи.

Це можливість не просто приєднатися до існуючої структури, а фактично побудувати нову investment vertical з нуля: від underwriting framework та investment strategy до запуску institutional-grade debt vehicle у перспективі.



ПРО КОМПАНІЮ

Roosh Investment Group — українська інвестиційна група, яка розвиває та масштабує технологічні бізнеси глобально. Група працює як інвестор і оператор, поєднуючи капітал, підприємницький досвід і глибоку експертизу в технологічних ринках.

Основні напрями:

Roosh Ventures — VC-напрям, який інвестує у Pre-seed to Series A компанії в enterprise SaaS, fintech, gaming та AI-driven продукти в Європі та США.

Roosh X — growth-stage investment and co-building platform, що фокусується на зрілих технологічних бізнесах у AI/ML, Gaming, Fintech, Consumer Apps.

Також група управляє портфелем публічних equities, fixed income інструментів і розглядає нові напрями.

Компанія вже має:

 - існуючий deal flow;

 - доступ до tech ecosystem;

 - внутрішню експертизу в AI, fintech, gaming та consumer tech;

 - стартовий інвестиційний капітал для запуску напряму.



ЩО БУДЕ У ЗОНІ ВІДПОВІДАЛЬНОСТІ

 - Формування investment strategy для debt products;

 - Побудова underwriting framework та risk approach;

 - Аналіз бізнесів, cash flow та unit economics;

 - Структурування debt deals;

 - Ведення pipeline та пошук нових opportunities;

 - Робота з venture debt / revenue-based financing structures;

 - Побудова monitoring та portfolio management processes;

 - Взаємодія з legal / finance / external advisors;

 - Формування команди та операційної моделі напряму;

 - Участь у potential future fund formation.



КОГО ШУКАЮТЬ

 - Людину з сильним бекграундом у private debt/venture debt/structured lending/mezzanine financing/tech-focused credit products.

 - Досвід прийняття інвестиційних рішень;

 - Вміння будувати процеси з нуля;

 - Сильне розуміння risk assessment;

 - Комфорт у fast-moving та entrepreneurial environment;

 - Високий рівень автономності;

 - Готовність бути owner нового напряму, а не лише execution lead.


NICE TO HAVE

 - Досвід у venture debt або revenue-based financing;

 - LP / fund formation exposure;

 - Experience with tech ecosystem;

 - Network у PE / VC ecosystem;

 - European market exposure.



ЩО РОБИТЬ РОЛЬ ЦІКАВОЮ

 - Можливість побудувати новий investment direction практично з нуля;

 - Високий рівень ownership;

 - Реальний вплив на investment strategy;

 - Доступ до existing tech ecosystem та deal flow;

 - Потенційний шлях до future institutional vehicle / fund structure;

 - Довгострокова роль із partner-level upside.



Якщо ця роль вам відгукується — будемо раді познайомитися! Надішліть, будь ласка, своє резюме та будь-які додаткові матеріали, які вважаєте релевантними.

Ми розглянемо вашу заявку протягом п’яти робочих днів і, якщо ваш досвід відповідатиме тому, що ми шукаємо, зв’яжемося з вами, щоб домовитися про дзвінок і ближче познайомитися.

We are toogeza, a Ukrainian recruiting company focused on hiring talents and building teams for tech startups worldwide. People make a difference in the big game — and we help find the right ones.

Currently, we are looking for an experienced Account Executive to join one of Toogeza’s clients operating at the intersection of deep tech, infrastructure, and creative industries.




YOU WOULD BE RUNNING SUCH TASKS AS:

 - Owning the full sales cycle end-to-end — from first contact and discovery to deal closing and handoff to delivery, with a high level of autonomy;

 - Building and scaling sales processes from scratch, including discovery, qualification, pipeline management, forecasting, and internal alignment;

 - Running high-quality discovery calls with senior technical and business stakeholders, uncovering real customer pain points and mapping them to business value (not just product features);

 - Developing and maintaining a strong, relationship-driven sales pipeline through outbound efforts, partnerships, and industry presence;

 - Representing the company at industry events, conferences, and trade shows to generate new opportunities and long-term relationships;

 - Leading customer dinners, private meetings, and executive-level conversations to build trust-based, long-term partnerships;

 - Translating customer and market feedback into clear, actionable insights for product and engineering teams to influence roadmap, prioritization, and positioning;

 - Working closely with founders, product, and engineering to ensure strong alignment between customer needs and product development;

 - Taking ownership not only of revenue, but also of how sales is built, scaled, and executed within the company.




REQUIRED SKILLS AND EXPERTISE:

 - Proven experience in B2B sales or business development within deep-tech, infrastructure, or technically complex products;

 - Strong technical intuition or background, with the ability to confidently communicate with engineers, technical artists, TDs, CTOs, and other technical decision-makers;

 - Solid understanding of the VFX and/or Gaming industries, including studio workflows, production pipelines, constraints, and buying dynamics (strong plus);

 - Experience selling complex solutions rather than simple SaaS products;

 - Ability to operate effectively in an early-stage environment with ambiguity, minimal process, and high ownership;

 - Strong executive presence and communication skills, including at the C-level;

 - Relationship-oriented mindset with a focus on long-term value rather than transactional sales;

 - Willingness and ability to represent the company at events and travel as needed.




LEADERSHIP & GROWTH POTENTIAL:

 - This is the first dedicated sales role in the company, with a clear path toward sales leadership as the organization scales;

 - Opportunity to hire, mentor, and build a high-performing sales team over time;

 - Founder-level mindset — treating company success as personal responsibility and taking ownership beyond a defined job description.




WHAT’S NEXT?

If this role sounds like a fit — we’d love to hear from you! Just send over your CV and anything else you’d like us to consider.

We’ll review your application within five working days, and if your background aligns with what we’re looking for, we’ll get in touch to schedule a call and get to know each other better.

We are toogeza, a Ukrainian recruiting company that is focused on hiring talents and building teams for tech startups worldwide. People make a difference in the big game, and we may help to find the right ones.

Currently, we are looking for an experienced User Acquisition Manager to join one of toogeza’s clients.

Requirements

 - 2+ years of experience in user acquisition/performance marketing;

 - Experience managing budgets over $100K on Meta;

 - Strong understanding of key marketing metrics (CPM, CTR, CPC, CR, CPA, ROAS, ROI, LTV, CAC, Churn, Retention) and how they impact business performance;

 - Strong analytical skills and ability to make data-driven decisions;

 - Experience working with Amplitude/Tableau;

 - Structured thinking and systematic work approach;

 - Creativity and ability to generate high-quality ideas and hypotheses;

 - Ability to explain and support your decisions with data;

 - Ability to react quickly and adapt to changes;

 - Intermediate or higher level of English.

Responsibilities

 - Creating, managing, and scaling advertising campaigns (Meta and others);

 - Optimizing ad campaigns to achieve KPIs;

 - Owning key performance metrics such as ROAS, Spend, and others;

 - Developing and testing hypotheses to optimize user acquisition performance;

 - Working closely with PMMs and the creative team to enhance the product and ad creatives;

 - Participating in creative brainstorming sessions and generating new ideas;

 - Researching and analyzing competitors’ user acquisition strategies, including their channels and ad creatives.

What we offer

 - Remote or Hybrid work. The choice is yours!;

 - Time-off Policy — unlimited Out of office days;

 - Sport and education compensations;

 - Psychologists compensation;

 - Language courses compensation;

 - Coworking compensation;

 - Health insurance;

 - 100% Sick Leave Compensation;

 - Team buildings and offsites (Spain, Italy, Poland and other);

 - Merch;

 - Birthday presents.

What’s next?

If this role sounds like a fit — we’d love to hear from you! Just send over your CV and anything else you’d like us to consider.

We’ll review everything within five working days, and if your background matches what we’re looking for, we’ll get in touch to set up a call and get to know each other better.
